10E+63   vigintillions



Decimal (nth) Places:
* Just use a suffix (-t)



Integers:
[NEG]  -3   -2   -1    0    1    2    3  [POS]

If negative, add "neg" before the number
Else then, add "fos" before the number, or even without "fos"
examples     read as
  -40      neg vadzye
   51      fos vidzyeozn, vidzyeozn



Decimal Points:
* If the number has a decimal point, the "." read as /dot/ (o in dog)
examples        read as
  21.01     dozyeozn dot zyet
 -21.1      neg dozyeozn dot ozn
  3.4121    tri dot vadmilt ozndant dozyeozn
 -3.4121    neg tri dot vadmilt ozndant dozyeoznt

     


